HEXDUMP(1)                       User Commands                      HEXDUMP(1)

NAME
       hexdump - display file contents in hexadecimal, decimal, octal,
       or ASCII

SYNOPSIS
       hexdump [OPTION]... [FILE]...

DESCRIPTION
       The hexdump utility is a filter which displays the specified files,
       or standard input if no files are specified, in a user specified
       format.

OPTIONS
       -b     one-byte octal display

       -c     one-byte character display

       -C     canonical hex+ASCII display

       -d     two-byte decimal display

       -e FORMAT
              specify a format string

       -f FILE
              specify a format file

       -n LENGTH
              interpret only LENGTH bytes of input

       -o     two-byte octal display

       -s OFFSET
              skip OFFSET bytes from the beginning

       -v     display all input data (do not squeeze duplicate lines)

       -x     two-byte hexadecimal display (default)

       -h, --help
              display this help and exit

       -V, --version
              output version information and exit

   OFFSET and LENGTH accept suffixes:
       b (*512), k or K (*1024), m or M (*1048576), and 0x prefix for
       hexadecimal values.

   FORMAT STRING (-e):
       Format: [repeat/byte_count] "format_string"
       Conversions: %d %i %u %o %x %X %c %s %_ad %_ax %_ao %_c %_p %_u

NOTES
       Duplicate lines are replaced with a single '*' unless -v is given.
       Default format (no options) is -x (two-byte hex).

